description: Three Bangladeshi citizens fell victim to a kidney trafficking ring in India. Lured by promises of employment, they were instead subjected to forced kidney removal under the guise of medical tests. The victims received inadequate compensation and have returned to Bangladesh to share their ordeal, prompting a chargesheet and forthcoming trial.

It also aims to speed up sex crime and acid attack trials and demands stricter punishments for disclosing survivors' identities. description: Day 6 of the Paris Paralympics sees Indian athletes competing in shooting, archery and athletics. Avani Lekhara and Mona Agarwal will be in the Women's 50m rifle 3 positions SH1 event. Archer Pooja and several athletes in shot put, high jump, javelin, and 400m race will also compete.

After discussing 49 names, the party's central election committee cleared 34, while further discussion continues. For J&K elections, the party released its second list of six candidates and is cooperating with National Conference, contesting 32 and 51 seats respectively.

He set a new Paralympics record with a throw of 70.59 meters, surpassing his Tokyo mark. Sumit joins Avani Lekhara in the exclusive club of Indian athletes with consecutive Paralympic wins.

Road crashes account for over 43% of unintentional injury deaths in India

description: As Jammu gears up for assembly elections after a ten-year gap, residents are eager to vote amid ongoing terrorism threats and local issues. Remote villages are hosting political meetings where concerns about healthcare, infrastructure, and security dominate. People hope for a government that will address their needs for the first time in years.

description: A 40-year-old pest controller named Tapas Paul from Kolkata was arrested on Sunday for allegedly molesting a woman during a protest against the rape and murder of an RG Kar PGT doctor. description: A Delhi court has ordered a four-day ED custody for AAP MLA Amanatullah Khan in a money laundering investigation connected to alleged irregularities in the Delhi Waqf Board and disproportionate assets. After allegedly being uncooperative and appearing only once out of 14 summonses post a Supreme Court direction, the ED arrested Khan.

description: A 23-year-old woman was injured in a drone-based bomb attack in Manipur's Imphal West district, the second such incident in two days. The attack happened at Senjam Chirang, causing abdominal injuries to the woman, who is now stable in hospital. Security forces responded quickly as militants also fired from a nearby hilltop.

description: Gold Star families have criticized Kamala Harris for the deaths of US military personnel during the Kabul withdrawal. Gen. H.R. McMaster also highlighted Trump's role in the debacle through negotiations with the Taliban. The controversy was further fueled when Trump attended a memorial event, sparking divided opinions among families and military personnel.

description: India's cabinet committee on security has cleared a Rs 26,000 crore deal to acquire 240 aero-engines for the Sukhoi-30MKI jets. These engines, to be produced by Hindustan Aeronautics Limited (HAL) with significant indigenous content, aim to bolster the Indian Air Force's capabilities. This order follows the recent acquisition of additional Sukhoi jets and upgrades for other aircraft.

description: John Cena and Shay Shariatzadeh's relationship began in 2019 and evolved quietly, emphasizing their mutual respect. Despite an age gap, their connection is robust. description: At least four people were killed on Monday in a shooting on a Chicago subway train at the Forest Park station on the Blue Line. The suspect fled but was later caught on a separate train route. Vital security camera footage helped law enforcement with their investigation into the incident.
title: Four killed in Chicago subway shooting; suspect arrested

description: The Cabinet Committee on Security approved the purchase of 240 AL-31FP aero-engines for the Indian Air Force’s Su-30 MKI aircraft from Hindustan Aeronautics Limited at a cost exceeding Rs 26,000 crore. With over 54% indigenous content, the engines will be delivered over the next eight years, enhancing operational readiness. Su-30 MKI is one of the most powerful and strategically-significant fleet of IAF.

description: Teacher’s Day is a time to appreciate the essential role teachers play in shaping our lives, beyond textbooks to life's important lessons. This piece highlights ways to show gratitude through heartfelt messages and quotes. It emphasizes that despite technological advances, teachers' human connection and wisdom are irreplaceable.
title: Happy teachers day 2024: Wishes, messages & more to share with your teachers

description: Dr. Sandip Ghosh, former principal of Kolkata’s RG Kar Medical College, was arrested for corruption. The CBI, investigating financial irregularities, acted after the Calcutta high court's directive. Following a tragic rape and murder incident at the college, Ghosh resigned and was later suspended by the Indian Medical Association. Ghosh resigned from his role on August 12, just three days after the incident.

description: The Mamata Banerjee government will present the Aparajita Woman and Child Bill, proposing the death penalty for rapists whose crimes result in the victim's death or vegetative state. description: French IT company Atos has revised its financial forecasts, lowering its 2024 revenue projection to $10.72 billion due to a weaker business environment and contract delays. description: Bank lockers are a secure option for storing valuables like jewellery and documents. To access a locker, select a bank near you with good service and an account requirement. It is important to note that banks are not liable for contents of the locker.

description: The Supreme Court provided bail to Arvind Kejriwal's aide, Bibhav Kumar, in the assault case involving Swati Maliwal. Kumar had been in custody for 100 days, with a detailed 500-page chargesheet filed by Delhi Police. description: Tech Mahindra’s Anand Mahindra has featured Paralympic archer Sheetal Devi in his Monday motivation post, praising her resilience and courage. description: The Cabinet has allocated approximately Rs 14,000 crore for initiatives to improve the agriculture sector. description: The RSS supports the caste census, stressing it should be used solely for the welfare of underprivileged communities and not for political purposes. description: Under the leadership of Muhammad Yunus, Bangladesh's interim government is contemplating a review of MoUs and infra projects with India. description: Vijay Shekhar Sharma of Paytm shared a video of Steve Jobs stating that sales and marketing roles are often prioritized over product innovation in tech companies. She hasn't competed since the Singapore Open last year.

description: A fatal bus accident occurred in Mumbai's Lalbaugh area when an intoxicated passenger caused the driver to lose control. The incident involved a BEST bus on route no. 66, injuring nine people and causing one death. The police have detained the intoxicated passenger and initiated an investigation to uncover further details.

description: The Supreme Court has established a high-level committee to engage with farmers protesting at the Shambhu border. The court, acknowledging a significant trust deficit between the government and farmers, has tasked the committee to commence discussions within a week. description: Avani Lekhara won her second gold medal at the Paralympic Games in the women’s 10m air rifle standing SH1 event. description: The National Medical Commission (NMC) has issued new guidelines for the Competency-Based Medical Education (CBME) Curriculum, effective from the 2024-25 MBBS batch. The revised curriculum emphasizes outcome-based, patient-centric learning, ethical values, and communication skills through a new "AETCOM" module. Aimed at creating competent Indian Medical Graduates, the guidelines integrate subjects horizontally and vertically and focus on preparing students for real-life medical scenarios, aligning with global standards.

description: The Supreme Court of India deliberated on the legality of bulldozing properties solely due to criminal charges against the owners. The bench stressed that demolitions must follow legal protocols. Solicitor General Tushar Mehta affirmed that properties can't be bulldozed for criminal associations.  The term 'Bulldozer justice,' as referred to by the public, is a form of instant justice mechanism involving the razing of houses, shops, or any premises belonging to individuals accused of a crime.

description: During September 2024, banks in various states will observe 15 days of holidays, including Ganesh Chaturthi, Milad-un-Nabi, and the Birthday of Maharaja Hari Singh Ji.

description: As winter season nears, Emirates and other northern airlines are set to transition to winter schedules on October 27. Emirates will extensively utilise its 615-seat Airbus A380s, focusing on high-volume, lower-premium-demand routes. Twelve routes, including Bangkok, Gatwick, and Manchester, will be served between November and February, marking a strategic shift in capacity deployment.

description: SME IPOs are attracting a surge of retail investors, with the average number of applicants skyrocketing to 219,000 in FY25. Listing gains make these IPOs highly appealing, but Sebi has issued advisories urging caution.

description: Pakistan's Babar Azam is enduring a lean patch in Test cricket, evident in the second Test against Bangladesh in Rawalpindi. Despite posting 274 in the first innings, Pakistan faced resilience from Bangladesh, thanks to a Litton Das and Mehidy Hasan Miraz partnership. Babar's continued poor form is a significant concern among fans and critics.

description: The Enforcement Directorate detained AAP MLA Amanatullah Khan in connection with a money laundering case related to the Waqf Board. The charges are based on a CBI FIR and multiple Delhi Police complaints, alleging illegal recruitment and personal gains made during Khan's tenure as chairman from 2018 to 2022.

description: Rahul Gandhi addressed the employment conditions of Delhi Transport Service (DTC) employees, highlighting their lack of job security and social benefits. Highlighting their plight and delayed salaries, he questioned why permanent citizens have temporary jobs. Gandhi urged the government for equal work and pay, stressing the essential role of these workers in Delhi's public transport system.

description: The ministry of Information and Broadcasting called Netflix's content head regarding the controversial web series 'IC-814 -- The Kandahar Hijack'. Amit Malviya criticized this depiction, suggesting it could alter historical understanding, while Omar Abdullah pointed out similar issues with past films.

description: Kangana Ranaut voiced criticism against the OTT series 'IC 814: The Kandahar Hijack' for alleged historical distortion serving political agendas. description: Hindalga jail inmates in Belagavi protested for access to tobacco products after viral photos showed actor Darshan smoking inside Bengaluru Central Prison. Over 500 undertrials skipped breakfast and threatened to miss lunch unless their demands were met. The Karnataka government subsequently suspended nine prison officials due to the incident.

description: Litton Das's 138-run knock and significant stand with Mehidy Hasan Miraz led Bangladesh to recover from 26/6 to 262 all out in the second Test against Pakistan at Rawalpindi. description: Reliance Retail-backed Dunzo has laid off 75% of its workforce to curb costs and manage financial challenges.

description: Rohit Sharma's captaincy, often compared to MS Dhoni's, is praised for his tactical insights and relaxed team environment by Ravichandran Ashwin. description: Apple plans to unveil the iPhone 16 series on September 9, featuring four variants: iPhone 16, iPhone 16 Plus, iPhone 16 Pro, and iPhone 16 Pro Max. The new series will include upgrades like larger displays, a new titanium finish, an A18 chipset, enhanced cameras, bigger batteries, and 40W fast charging for the Pro models.

Trudeau emphasized Canadian unity and support, highlighting the upcoming federal election scheduled for October 20, 2025.

description: Elon Musk faces online mockery after accidentally referring to his rebranded social media platform X as Twitter. Musk's recent slip, amidst controversy and loss of market value, highlights ongoing identity challenges.

description: Former cricketer and father of Yuvraj Singh, Yograj Singh criticized ex-India captains MS Dhoni and Kapil Dev. description: In a recent study, scientists propose that the universe might have contracted before the Big Bang, creating primordial black holes that could explain dark matter. Future gravitational wave detectors may confirm this hypothesis, revolutionizing our understanding of dark matter and the universe’s origins.

description: Torrential rains across Telangana caused severe waterlogging in low-lying areas and disrupted daily routines. Lakes, tanks, and streams overflowed, isolating many villages and damaging railway tracks, which led to numerous train cancellations. In a dramatic rescue, a 50-year-old daily laborer swep away by the current while crossing a flooded culvert was saved by local youths and policemen.

description: NASA astronaut Butch Wilmore, on the International Space Station, reported a strange sonar-like noise from the Boeing Starliner. Mission Control is investigating. Wilmore and Sunita Williams, having extended their stay due to technical issues, are set to return in 2025 on a SpaceX Dragon capsule. The Starliner will return to Earth soon.
title: 'Like a sonar ping': Stranded Nasa astronaut hears 'strange noises' from Boeing Starliner

description: In Pakistan, a surge in mpox cases raises concerns with Peshawar confirming its fifth case this year. Authorities highlight the city's potential as a hub for infected travelers from the Gulf. Health screening at airports is intensified, and isolation wards are set up. Vigilance among travelers, especially from Saudi Arabia, is crucial to curb the virus spread.
title: Mpox fears escalate in Pakistan as fifth case detected in Peshawar

description: HDFC Bank has temporarily ended its five-year partnership with Apple due to cost-to-income concerns. This collaboration offered exclusive benefits to cardholders. Apple now partners with American Express, Axis Bank, and ICICI Bank. Despite the change, HDFC Bank expects significant growth during the upcoming festive season, especially with its revamped PayZapp app's growing user base.
title: HDFC Bank takes 'temporary break' from its Apple iPhone partnership

description: Yograj Singh, father of Yuvraj Singh, has strongly criticized MS Dhoni, accusing him of negatively impacting Yuvraj's cricket career, especially post-2014. Despite Yuvraj's significant contributions to India's 2007 T20 and 2011 ODI World Cup victories, Yograj believes his son's career was curtailed due to Dhoni's influence on team selection decisions.
title: 'I won't forgive Dhoni': Yuvraj's father Yograj criticizes former India captain

description: Bangladesh turned the tables in the second Test against Pakistan in Rawalpindi, going from 26-6 to a solid 262, propelled by Liton Das' 138 and Mehidy Hasan Miraz's 78. Pakistan closed the third day at 9-2. Ahmad Shahzad criticized Pakistan's inconsistent display while praising their young bowlers.
title: 'Bangladesh aya hi...': Pakistan slammed for conceding advantage

description: Mohammad Kaif recently posted a touching video of his 79-year-old father, Mohammad Tarif Ansari, displaying impressive batting skills. Tarif, previously a player for the Railways and Uttar Pradesh, continues to show remarkable fitness and technique. Kaif is renowned for his exceptional fielding and middle-order batting, notably in the 2002 NatWest Series final vs England.
title: Kaif in awe of 79-year-old father’s glorious drives

description: AAP MLA Amanatullah Khan claimed that the Enforcement Directorate (ED) came to his house to arrest him in a money laundering case related to the Waqf Board. He accused the agency of harassment and targeting his party members, stating the investigation has been ongoing since 2016 without proof of corruption according to the CBI.
title: 'ED team has reached my house to arrest me,' claims AAP MLA Amanatullah Khan

description: The search for Aditya Vardhan Singh, a deputy director in the UP health department, has entered its second day after he was swept away by the Ganga's strong currents while bathing at Nanamau Ghat. His friends allege that divers initially demanded money for rescue efforts. Authorities are now investigating these claims while continuing the search.
title: UP officer swept away by strong currents in Ganga; divers demanded Rs 10,000 to rescue him, say friends

description: The 2024 presidential race is highly competitive, with Vice President Kamala Harris narrowly ahead of Donald Trump. Recent polls by ABC News/Ipsos show Harris leading, particularly among women and in key battleground states. Both candidates are ramping up their campaigns as Election Day draws near, aiming to secure their respective bases.
title: Latest poll data: Kamala gains upper hand in key swing states, Trump trails

description: Tech billionaire Elon Musk has accused Brazilian Supreme Court Justice Alexandre de Moraes of election interference and labeled him a 'fake judge.' Musk claims former Twitter employees were aiding Moraes. This conflict arises from X's refusal to remove profiles promoting anti-democracy content, leading to significant fines from Brazil’s Supreme Federal Court.
title: Elon Musk on Brazil’s SC judge who banned X: “I’m sorry to say…”

description: Prince Harry, in his memoir Spare, shares a raw account of a heated argument with Meghan Markle, triggered by his deeper emotional issues. Emphasizing the importance of therapy and personal growth, he acknowledges Meghan's support in helping him confront his struggles, illustrating the real-life challenges in their relationship.
title: Prince Harry and Meghan Markle's heated argument: Duke snaps at wife, 'Why’s she having a go at me?'
Famed 'Russian spy' whale found dead in Norway; cause a mystery for now

description: Donald Trump's feeling of exclusion is highlighted as Melania and Barron converse in Slovenian, which Trump doesn't understand. Barron, who speaks multiple languages, stepped into the spotlight at a recent campaign rally. Melania's parents were significantly involved in Barron's upbringing, and Melania’s mother’s death in January 2024 had a profound impact on the family.
title: Trump feels left out as wife Melania and son Barron speak in secret code: 'It annoys him'

description: Reigning US Open champion Coco Gauff exited in the fourth round, losing to Emma Navarro amidst numerous errors. This comes after earlier eliminations of Novak Djokovic and Carlos Alcaraz. Navarro, who beat Gauff at Wimbledon, heads to the quarter-finals to face Paula Badosa.
title: US Open: Coco Gauff joins fallen stars after New York horror show
J'khand recruitment test deaths trigger political slugfest
